By Bashir Bello KANO — Not fewer than 201 Kano residents have been hospitalized after inhaling an expired chemical from a cylinder at a scrap metal collection point in the Sharada Industrial area of the state. It was gathered that the incident happened when a scrap man dismantled the cylinder and the expired chemical escaped into the air resulting in many residents inhaling the toxic substance coming down unconscious, coughing, and vomiting. Meanwhile, the Kano State Police Command on Saturday said it has cordoned off the scrap metal collection point where the chemical emission emanated. Confirming the incident, the state’s police spokesperson, SP Abdullahi Haruna said the ugly incident happened on Friday evening and it is yet to gather details of the incident. SP Haruna said, “We are yet to get details of the incidence. “We have cordoned off the area. And we have deployed experts to the area who have already swung into action,” the police public relations officer, SP Haruna said. On his part, the spokesperson of Kano State Fire Service, Saminu Yusif said it has furmigate and brought the situation in the area under control. “We have succeeded in bringing the situation under control. We got some experts from private firm with technical know-how about the situation who brought some chemical to control the emission. The chemical was mixed with water from our water tank to neutralize the expired chemical spread. “Several persons were evacuated to the hospital. While we were evacuating the victims, other good samaritans were also lending helping hand,” Yusif however stated. Earlier, officials of the National Emergency Management Agency, NEMA in the state puts the number of casualties affected in the incident at 201. The agency also said victims from the incident were rushed to Murtala Muhammad Specialist Hospital, Sharada Industrial Hospital and Ja’en Hospital, for medical attention.